
[1]belles-letters

   BELLES-LETTERS, n. plu. bel' letter, or anglicized, bell-letters.
   Polite literature; a word of very vague signification. It includes
   poetry and oratory; but authors are not agreed to what particular
   branches of learning the term should be restricted.
